yeah I think I am doing pretty good
5 star rb and qb and wr
might get another 4 star this round
yeah i only got two 5 stars
well is it on to next step
i think you can still look at tit
i dont care to look its not big deal
i got like 5 HBs not one over 90 speed
i am ready whenever you are
you can go past training results for me too
i dont need to see it
i am going to have to cut a bunch
i think i brought in 6 WRs
and like 3 of the ATH were wrs
yeah my ATH was a QB
so i cant complain about that
let me know when you are done looking over the results
my QBs ahead of him are SO and JU
only thing I don't like is my MLB is not inredibly fast
my team wont look much different than last years on Off
my defense will be a bit different
year three is my national championship year
I will tlak to you in a bit
that sucks that you dropped like that
he had 10 sacks last year as a soph
you should put him at RB haha
im going to try and set some sack records with him this year
i am all done the preseason shit
although i didnt see a schedule part yet
i dont want to miss that
so if you see that dont advance without me doing it
do you control him from the end very often?
its either him or my MLB
but i moved an OLB to MLB who is a preseason All American
so i might let the computer control him
didnt he go down a bunch?
like some but not a ton
i had a huge gap at MLB
the guy behind him at OLB was awesome too
so it would have been silly to sit one
I looked at moving a couple olb to mlb and the dropped like 5 points at least
yeah i mean he might have dropped that many
but it wasnt more than that
yeah he might have jumped back up too
he still made a preseason all american list
I still have my QB for one more year though
nope I still have a senior but I would be totally fine with my freshman
the number 1 QB in the top 100 has me in his top 3
he is an 83 overall with 86 speed
I don't even bother recruiting those guys
its cool my QB is only a junior
and his back up who i like MORE is a SOPH
i am surprised my QB didnt go pro
he has like a 75%+ completion percentage
i tried to start that True Freshman last year and thats how i lost to UMD
so he will just have to wait his turn
and had like 30 TDs last year and only 4 picks I think
my oline is solid and real young
my OL is solid but kinda old
I don't have any great players I dont think
my qb will be 90+ and RB and TE
other than that I am not sure I have any others
my WRs are much worse this year
dude i want to play now that i got a new team
how much longer you think you want to stay at GT?
not sure I am open to leaving whenever
you know I always love rebuilding
i just think i might be ready to dip at some point
although i have noticed it is hard to recruit stability if you hop around a lot
in my offline league i coached like 5 teams in 8 years
and committs that cared about stability didnt come
so i took the worst team in the country and have been there for three years
and they literally were the WORST team in the country
before me they had back to back no win seasons
it was like AMAZING when i could get 3 start recruits
but my HB was pretty good speed
so it took me three years but in my third he won the Heisman
and i won the Rose Bowl
my schedule every year is horrendous
my first year i went like 500
second year i did well and only lost to ND and Michigan
last year only lost to ND
my win in the rose bowl was amazing
i was down a TD with 2 min to go - driving to score. threw a INT at the 5 with 1 min on the clock.
3 stops with all my Time Outs
my returner of the year returned it to the 5 with 10 seconds to go
i scored on a TE out
then went for two to win it
that is when this game is amazing
i have a good stable of RBs this year so I think I have a shot
I am only worried about you
